Batman is the eleventh studio album by American recording 
artist Prince and is the soundtrack album to the 1989 film 
Batman. It was released on June 20, 1989 by Warner Bros. 
Records. As a Warner Bros. stablemate, Prince's involvement 
in the soundtrack was designed to leverage the media companys 
contract-bound talent as well as fulfill the artist's need for 
a commercial (if not critical) revival. The result was yet 
another multi-platinum successful cross-media enterprise by 
Warner Bros., in the vein of Purple Rain. The album was placed 
#1 on Billboard's album chart for six consecutive weeks. It sold 
nearly three million copies in the United States alone.
